		<td><b>Re: Homemade Game Genie-to-toploader adapter...</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Is there a source for the correct thickness PCB with NES-style contacts already attached?  I've had the darnedest time searching for one online (although it's not hard to find the female card-edge connector through DigiKey.)<br /><br />The other solution that's been tried is to use a NES to Famicom cart adapter, plus Famicom to NES card adapter, plus Game Genie, plus NES cart.  A very cumbersome combination, but it does work without having to do any soldering.  To that end, I spent ten minutes diving through a stack of Gyromite carts at my local used game shop until I found the elusive NES to Famicom cart adapter!

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


